reviews.text:
I recently dined at Fiery Nashville Hot Chicken and tried their Fiery Chicken Tenders with the "Electrical Fire" spice level. The food was absolutely amazing‚Äîperfectly crispy, flavorful, and the spice was intense but incredibly satisfying for heat lovers like me! The service was top-notch, with friendly and attentive staff who made the experience even better.

A small suggestion: I think drinks should be included in the meal price rather than charged separately, as it would enhance the overall value.It‚Äôs also worth noting that this is one of the few restaurants with HMS certification, which speaks to their quality and standards. Highly recommend checking them out for a spicy, delicious meal!

Friendly staff! Food was pretty good and came out quickly! However the facility definitely needs a DEEP cleaning. We bought a fountain drink and noticed a lot of mold caked up the dispenser. I did tell the staff at the front. But after saying something I did end up seeing multiple people come in afterwards and use the machine... It was kind of hard to enjoy the food after seeing that.

Small restaurant but beat the flavor and food to big restaurant, we tried few different wraps, burgers, chicken over rice but all were A+++ , seating limited, service was fast, location is good, price was average

I got the signature chicken sandwich and it was worth the hype. There was enough flavor to go with the kick. It came with fries and dipping sauce that complimented the combo. I think the price is fair at $12.99 for the sandwich and fries. The staff were friendly and helped me navigate the menu. I will definitely be returning to try some other options on their menu. 10/10.

Was soooo good! This place filled up fast but even with tons of guests they kept up with the orders. Anything you get will be great bc the chicken was delicious, mac and cheese so creamy and they are crinkle fries!
